Suspected gunmen on Saturday evening killed four workers in a mining site in Dong village of Jos North Local Government Area in Plateau State. Sources said the four men were shot dead while a woman, who survived gunshots, is receiving treatment in the hospital. A community leader Emmanuel Dong confirmed the attack. According to him, the attack occurred around 6 pm. Spokesman of the Plateau Police Command, ASP Gabriel Ubah confirmed the attack to The Nation. - Advertisement - Ubah, said: “We are aware of the attack and four people were killed.   112 illegal refineries discovered in Rivers council     2023: Obi missing as Atiku’s campaign team storms…     VIDEO: Go make us proud, Buhari charges Super Eagles   “The Command has deployed armed police men to the area and calm have returned.” Jos South/Jos East House of Representatives member Hon. Dachung Musa Bagos empathisised with families of the deceased. In a statement by his media adviser, Danja Dafwam, Bagos identified the victims as James Danboyi 30; Moses Peter Danboyi 24 and Livinus Pius Danboyi 19. The member said the incident has raised concerns over the readiness of security agencies to tackle once and for all the gorilla style of killing, which has been the case for more than two decades. He frowned at how easily small arms and light weapons find their ways indiscriminately into the country and move around without traces. He called on the Federal and State Governments to charge the security agencies to tackle more seriously the insecurity across board.